76561198042274594,Recommended,422900,25771298,"Posted: 29 September, 2016",all,Karl Marx,"Good length campaign. Simple to learn. Some areas are locked from the start needing a certain amount of missions completed first. That is until I realised there's literally a button saying ""unlock anyway"". Great idea for people re-downloading the game with a fresh save file. Great mission editor lets you design the worlds in great detail. Random mission generator for when you've completed the campaign and bonus levels.The random mission generator is perfect. Lets you change every single detail and variable.Creating, naming and using custom ships is an option as well. Easy to learn and use editor for that.This game has tons of replayability and is definitely worth buying. Haven't found any bugs either. A welcome fact considering the state of most games on day one."
,Recommended,422900,25801224,"Posted: 1 October, 2016",all,Druark,"A game about fighting an endless swarm with spaceships and occasionally your own swarm. Though not exactly intelligent (they just float around unless you go near them) you can get quickly overwhelmed if you don't pay attention and the campaign should take, even on 4x speed (which I don't recommend for your first playthrough) at least 3-5 hours.After you've completed the campaign which many will say is just a tutorial for custom missions, you can go and play with the simulator which is basically a skirmish mode, or you can mess with the map editor and create your own missions for others (or youself) to play. I haven't even played all the modes yet and I can say without a doubt this game is worth the price of £10.99. Its not very expensive for a game with tonnes of replayability, especially with the added ship designer which means you can design huge battleships or a fleet of tiny cheap fast frigates.Overall I'd give this an 8/10, the controls sometimes can be a bit annoying and you might want to rebind a few and some things like an encyclopedia to explain modules is missing but other than that, it's great :D"
