76561198005406191,Recommended,422900,31782508,Posted: 15 May,all,servvsumbrarum,"Greetings!  At its core Particle Fleet: Emergence is a simple game; sort of like playing against a virus.  You slowly capture territory and build ships while the enemy spreads out in all direction with an endless supply of particles (duh).  You will spend a good deal of time overwhelmed and barely holding on but this is part of the charm of the game.Difficult but Fair:  I almost consider this game a ‘souls-like’ game, the difficulty can be high but it is far and you will need to repeat some levels to adapt and understand the best approach.  Some tactics that work wonders on one level will be useless at another.  You have to evaluate your location, land mass, energy mines and the way your opponent is coming at you.  This ends in a satisfying victory when you do finally accomplish it and doesn’t take too long to pick up and put down.Simple and effective:  Every bit of this game is efficient and effective, no, the graphics aren’t award winning but they accomplish the game’s purpose and I’d argue that better graphics could ruin the game.  The music is amazing and although it would be nice to have a bit more I love the score that is in this game.  Mechanics are solid and so are the controls; overall just no real complaints.So, what’s bad:  I can’t really say that I have any part of this game I dislike?  Well, now that I think about it sometimes you get a point where the game is yours but it is going to take another 5-10 minutes to slowly make your way to victory.  This can be a bit boring at times but I don’t really see a way around it.  Overall, I love this game, especially for its price.  The story could be better but wasn’t really expecting anything on this front.All in all, if you like tactical games, especially those that are easy to pick up and a decent difficulty to ensure a satisfactory victory (or defeat) get this game.  It is well worth the play through and if you are like me you will find yourself picking it up from time to time.  Enjoy!"
