,Recommended,422900,25926576,"Posted: 8 October, 2016",all,alfanugan,"I have enjoyed Knuckle Cracker's games since Creeper World 1 and this is no exception.  In the Creeper World series you battle against a liquid enemy.  This time around you battle against particles that have their own physics.  The particles can bind together to create enemy objects and while you blast away at it with your missiles, cannons, and lasers you see the particles leave the object.A great strategy game that lets you pause the action, makes strategic moves, then resume to see how it unfolds.  It lets you play the levels as designed, or you can create your own fleet of ships with however many weapons you want to install and battle the levels that way.  A full map editor is included so you can design your own maps and submit online for others to try.  If you are really ambitious, it includes a scripting language that will let you design your own weapons, enemies, or AI.  A free demo is even available on Knuckle Cracker's website if you are unsure whether you would like this sort of game, give it a try!Countless hours of fun!"
