,Recommended,422900,25991157,"Posted: 11 October, 2016",all,Skel1,"Super Short TL;DR: If you liked creeper world 3, you will like this.Slightly longer TL:DR: While this game isn't a creeper world 3 sequel it shares very similar gameplay elements and can almost be called a spiritual sequal. The game is played by defending from and conquering never ending emitters of 'stuff'. In creeper world it was basically water (grey goo) that you held back with various towers. In this game you're holding back ""space grey goo"" and instead of using towers, you're using space ships that are each retrofitted with various types of guns.More formal review: Creative take on the tower defense genre. Instead of fighting waves of enemies, you're tasked with defeating a map that has a bunch of emitters that spawn unlimited enemies. The enemies in this game have a mostly fluid behavior similar to fighting a flow of water if that makes sense. Pacing through the story is good with incremental upgrades, and after a bit of progression the game opens up additional non-story maps and a community portal that can potentially offer an infinite number of maps to play.  Instead of building stationary towers you build space ships with retrofitted weapons that you can strategically place and move around the map at will.Highly recommended if you like tower defense game. If you have not played Knuckle Cracker's previous game creeper world 3 I highly recommend both, as the the games are very similar in many ways but different enough to offer a fresh experience."
