76561198006621260,Recommended,422900,25788478,"Posted: 30 September, 2016",all,Tarmandan,"Simple concept, upon which can, has been and will be built increasingly complex mechanics.Depending on the mission you have limited amounts of ships, energy sources and land units. Your enemy has emitters which spew out particles that move around the map and damage your stuff. You move your ships close, have enough firepower to kill newly spawned particles and bring special units in range to kill the emitters. Simple, right? Now add to that virtually infinite possibilities thanks to the built-in map editor and scripting language as well as the option to share your maps with other players.At the same time you can do any mission with a custom fleet instead of the intended one.The story, while not bad, is not exeptional. The story missions are well crafted to slowly introduce new elements to the player while not forcefully slowing down veterans.Besides the story there is a random map generator as well as maps hand crafted by other players (currently, 24 hours after launch, already several dozen. Additionally you can play around with the ship editor and design your own awesome ships.If you have played the previous Creeper World games, then this game offers far more dynamic gameplay while at the same time allowing for far more customization.If you like strategy games in general, you should try it out, if feels different to other strategy games and might just satisfy an urge you did not even realize you had.If you don't really like strategy games you should still try it out for the same reason: it is different to almost all other strategy games.If you absolutly dislike strategy games, why are you even here? That strategy tag should tell you everything you need to know.A really nice meal or a game that potentially can keep you busy for hours upon hours, you choose.tl;dr: If you do not hate strategy games then try this one, it is basically it's own subgenre."
