76561198023681981,Recommended,422900,33408865,Posted: 9 July,all,stayprest,"Particle Fleet: Emergence is the turtling game to end all turtling games which suited me down to the ground. Game balance on the campaign is good as are most of the extra scenarios although it gets a bit hit and miss with the community made scenarios some of which seem downright impossible whilst others are too trivial. The graphics are good, especially if you zoom right in on the ships but in practice it's more helpful to stay zoomed well out as this game is definitely more about grand strategy than micro-management.Set in space the game sees you obtaining licences to operate starships and land bound bases called omnis. Once you emerge into redacted space you will quickly be confronted with particles that will destroy your ships if allowed to build up too much. most scenarios involve destroying all enemy structures to win. In essence it's really a puzzle game set in space.Pros:Nice Graphics and soundEasy to save and return later for short sessionsGood value with over 30 hours of content with the provided scenarios and a random generator if you want to keep plauingLots of user generated contentCons:User generated content is a bit patchyI felt that more could have been made of the HQ ship, it is so fragile, so important and so useless that there is not much option but to leave it well behind your front lines which is kind of sad reallyAll in all I recommend this game if you like puzzle or strategy games especially if you like them set in space."
