76561198022030101,Recommended,422900,30152228,Posted: 24 February,all,Mr. Licious,"I've never written a Steam review before, not in six years of gaming and thousands of hours on Steam. This game compelled me to do it. I've followed this developer since they made flash games, and for years I wanted to find a way to support them. I'm so happy to see their games make it to Steam and happier still that innovation and iteration are well balanced in new titles. But enough pre-ramle.This game has tight mechanics, compelling difficulty progression, and constantly presents new challenges and tools to overcome them. While giving you a myriad number of paths to victory, and clearly laying out how each asset functions, it doesn't necessarily hold your hand. Rather than direct tutorials, the members of the game's cast of characters report to each other as things happen and allow you to fill in the gaps and discover ways to utilize incoming mechanics.It's just a great game to experience, a fun brain challenge, and a concise experience with some replayability to boot!"
